[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Investigating native issues**\n\nIt seems there might be a native issue with Class.getName related to how native-image performs static analysis. It’s possible that while it sees class literals, it doesn’t include constructors for reflection. If there's no metadata, it might not work. I wonder if we could avoid custom classes to lessen the reflection metadata requirements by using default provider classes instead. The user is asking about coverage, not running tests, so I need to inspect the reflection calls covered with Jacoco after edits, not execution.\n\n**Examining configuration and decryption**\n\nI’m considering using JSch.setConfig to configure provider classes that are currently unavailable, which may cause Class.forName to throw an error if I try newInstance. I can write a key to an encrypted form and load it using KeyPair.load, but I wonder if decrypting will work if the cipher is null. It seems that during the decrypt process, if the cipher isn’t initialized, it might not function properly. \n\nI think I could check if using `keyPair.writePrivateKey(String)` in the first test will help. The report shows coverage there due to running IdentityFileTest writeIdentityFile, but I'm still uncertain about `getFingerPrint`.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_084e66faf3526e510169fb9e09aea8819088ec0d26972ba837\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-54ZBgSWGaP5sn-QIlsNrbadU3mcW54iL_golAo4uFmrQDS1TwkeUpXgjTHKuy1TyCvt2Z24qDnIfv9bxIblO28_IQBFfSOmEkIwumfXPTXSPi7cTgchmhaZS0egu8UIDG7NtFPuNCIKv1iJXIZ-_vzMvxtfadvdNZDJqY8_-wYS7BaOrgKzS7Dg8pA18MyONSW32G_mQt3SHe6T97XoExTpel6AerMZAqOAzBkf43RZeLHswWsMKeymGrJ8HoJUHS0DywupDUL0lBlR1wCv0yhWUvP4-GOHKJQL884P7U3FLBjvWZK3GQd3K5ZKHbwQLXmj4OSxToBqKqYxxjrQN9WWJX4q2tPr9CDMd44oGnywz-klSGLBkYb5X8w7_x8YZPGIFcjTb24X7u3UpGDuNKqENH2f2_iwtO8dfWYToBD_9Hf952DLMo89U3TJyaQjOdqQw0dY5i__qjOzXeV3KIB2ODbulGp93wpww0Wp0bQVtQ6KQ