.load, but I wonder if decrypting will work if the cipher is null. It seems that during the decrypt process, if the cipher isn’t initialized, it might not function properly. \\n\\nI think I could check if using `keyPair.writePrivateKey(String)` in the first test will help. The report shows coverage there due to running IdentityFileTest writeIdentityFile, but I'm still uncertain about `getFingerPrint`.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_avi38C6EX83eFEd8QFUqfZYf|fc_084e66faf3526e510169fb9e19363c819097eb21ecaf10c28d", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git diff -- tests/src/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/src/test/java/com_jcraft/jsch/KeyPairTest.java tests/src/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/src/test/java/com_jcraft/jsch/IdentityFileTest.java | head -300"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 680, "output": 1017, "cacheRead": 47616, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 49313, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778097671756, "responseId": "resp_084e66faf3526e510169fb9e08f0c881909c1da48b7230e785"}}
